.TH YRRD 1 "May 2026" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
yrrd \- word frequency utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B yrrd
.I file
.RB [ \-w
.IR word1
.RI [ word2
.IR word3 ...]]
.br
.B yrrd
.B \-help
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B yrrd
reads a text file and counts word frequencies. Results are written to
.I results.txt
and printed to standard output.
.PP
A worker subprocess is forked via
.BR execl (3)
to handle file mapping and counting, keeping the parent process clean for output display.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I file
Path to the input text file. Required unless
.B \-help
is specified.
.TP
.BI \-w " word1 " [ word2 " " word3 ]
Count only the specified words (up to 3). If omitted, all words are counted.
.TP
.B \-help
Print usage information and exit.
.SH OUTPUT
Results are displayed as a two-column table:
.PP
.nf
COUNT      WORD
--------------------
42         the
17         quick
.fi
.PP
Results are also written to
.I results.txt
in the current directory.
.SH EXAMPLES
Count all words in a file:
.PP
.nf
    yrrd document.txt
.fi
.PP
Count only specific words:
.PP
.nf
    yrrd document.txt \-w hello world
.fi
.SH LIMITATIONS
Only supports up to 3 target words with
.BR \-w .
The results file
.I results.txt
is always written to the current working directory.
Hash table size is fixed at 1024 buckets.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
File not found, unsupported argument count, or other error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR wc (1),
.BR grep (1),
.BR sort (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Written by the yrrd project.